article.headline: Washington 61, Portland 49
article.story:
SEATTLE --  Regina Rogers scored 19 of her 26 points in the second half to lead Washington past Portland 61-49 on Friday night.

Rogers made 7 of 9 shots in the second half after missing five shots in the first half. She also had a game-high nine rebounds.

Jazmine Davis added 13 points for Washington (6-2), which rallied from a 27-24 halftime deficit to win its third straight game. The Huskies are off to their best start since going 9-2 in 2005-06.

Natalie Day scored 18 and Nakeisha Brown 15 to lead Portland (5-5), which dropped its third consecutive game. Only four players scored for the Pilots.

The Huskies improved to 10-0 against Portland since the series began in 1979.
